```{r}
#| echo: false
Vehicle_Insurance |> group_by(Gender) |> summarize(Avg_Premium = mean(annual_premium_usd))
```

According to the charts, age and gender was not a major component to one's annual premium.

#### Discussion:

My first assumption was proven wrong since age did not seem to dictate a major price difference with annual premiums. I still believe that there are other factors that apply to an annual premium like amount of accidents, type of vehicle, and more.

